author: pcl
msg: made ProductDerivations a bit more fault-tolerant -- when a failure occurs while loading ProductDerivation instances defined in services files, the system continues to start up with the ProductDerivations that did load, and a warning is printed to stderr. Note that this means that people using the uber-jar in 1.3 or 1.4 environments, or without having javax.persistence in their classpath, for example, will see warnings on stderr.
